other_tests.findings: The appendix is mildly distended measuring 7 mm in diameter and containing fluid within its lumen. Its walls are equivocally thickened. There is trace free fluid adjacent to the appendix. The colon is otherwise unremarkable. The small bowel is normal. The liver, kidneys, adrenals, spleen, and pancreas are within normal limits. No hydronephrosis or adenopathy is noted. The bone marrow signal is normal.
